Lagos State governor, Mr Babajide Sanwo-Olu, on Monday mourned the death of Oniru of Iruland, Oba Idowu Oniru, who passed on at 82, expressing grief over the death of the monarch. The late monarch, whose first son was former Commissioner for Waterfronts and Infrastructures, Adesegun Oniru, was said to have passed on during a brief illness. The governor, in his reaction, commiserated with the  Royal Family on the transition of the oba who joined his forebears. Buhari unfolds plans to reverse climate change in Nigeria N90bn election fund: Your allegations against Osinbajo are… Lagos-Ibadan rail: Amaechi berates CCECC for slow pace of… How FG policy on diversification can work ―Oyetola ALSO READ: Beauty West Africa Expo will boost local SME visibility Sanwo-Olu, in a short statement on his twitter handle, described the late monarch as a rare gem and a blessing to the state, saying his service to the state and country at large would remain his enduring legacy. “On behalf of the government and people of Lagos, I commiserate with the Oniru Royal Family on the transition of HRH Oba Idowu Oniru who joined his forebears. His service to the state and country at large will remain his enduring legacy,” he said. Here is how i overcome QUICK RELEASE and make it BIGGER, STRONGER And LONGER with this NAFDAC APPROVED NATURAL REMEDY. Click now!!